# COSMOS — Interactive Space Storytelling Website

COSMOS is an interactive educational web project focused on astronomy and space exploration.  
It presents scientific concepts through a cinematic scrolling experience, combining modern UI, immersive visuals, animations, and 3D elements.

The project was built as both:
- an interactive physics presentation
- a flagship front-end portfolio piece

## Overview

The website guides the user through a structured journey across major astronomy topics:

- The Universe
- Types of Galaxies
- The Milky Way
- The Solar System
- Voyager 1
- Final Quiz

Instead of feeling like a static school presentation, the experience is designed as a storytelling website with smooth transitions, visual hierarchy, and interactive exploration.

## Features

- Cinematic single-page scrollytelling experience
- Modern space-themed UI
- Interactive educational sections
- 3D Solar System built with Three.js
- Smooth animations powered by GSAP and ScrollTrigger
- Galaxy and Voyager themed visual storytelling
- Quiz section for knowledge recap
- Responsive structure for modern browsers

## Tech Stack

- HTML5
- CSS3
- SCSS
- Vanilla JavaScript (ES6+)
- Three.js
- GSAP
- ScrollTrigger

## Project Structure

```bash
space-project/
